1.Enable Multi-Factor Authentication.
Adds extra layer of security.
2.Use Strong Password Policies.
Prevents unauthorized access.
3.Update Systems Regularly.
Fixes vulnerabilities.
4.Install Antivirus Software.
Protects against malware.
5.Conduct Employee Security Training.
Reduces human errors.
6.Perform Regular Backups.
Protects against ransomware.
7.Restrict User Permissions.
Limits unauthorized access.
8.Encrypt Sensitive Data.
Protects confidential information.
9.Monitor Network Activity.
Detects suspicious behavior.
10.Perform Security Audits.
Identifies weaknesses early.
